{
  "stem": "18581.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said that the war is imminent and Jewish life is in danger, and that whoever can save himself should save himself.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And some young people, especially from countries closer to the Mediterranean, were able to do it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were in a more difficult situation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was too small.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father was, you know, had a family, a-- a wife, and a business, and so on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And most of us also didn't know when it will happen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Jews postponed and postponed, until it was probably too late.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then Poland fell apart and the Russians came and and so on, and-- All right.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let's just-- we're just going to complete some comments about your education.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "After you finished the gymnasium, you decided to go to Vilna University.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Was it hard or easy to get into the university?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was not difficult in-- the difficulty for Jews was only if they wanted to study medicine or agriculture.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Or law.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I wanted to study economics and government.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there was no problem in that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was also no problem in chemistry.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, you have to understand that in Lithuania, 80% of the doctors were Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And 84% of the lawyers were Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the nationalist government, egged on by maybe also anti-Semitic propaganda to some extent, wanted to Lithuanize the professionals more.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, they wanted to see more Lithuanian doctors and more Lithuanian lawyers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1939, it was already a little different.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was not the same government that was since 1926.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because after having suffered a ultimatum from Poland to drop demands for Vilna-- Vilnius-- Vilna, in Polish-- and having lost in March '39, Memel, to the Germans, to the Nazis, the Lithuanian government had to be expanded to include also the left and the right.",
      "word_count": 45
    }
  ],
